mixin events(data)
    section.events#events
        .events__container.container
            .events__title-wrap.wow.fadeInLeft(data-wow-offset="300")
                +title("EVENTS", "title_color_white events__title")
            ul.events__cards.wow.fadeInLeft(data-wow-offset="300")
                li.events__card
                    .events__img-wrap
                        picture
                            source(srcset="../assets/img/events-card-img1.webp", type="image/webp")
                            img.events__img(src="../assets/img/events-card-img1.jpg", alt="black car")
                    .events__card-content
                        +title("offroad to monte desert", "title_theme_card events__card-title")
                        ul.events__card-puncts
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-calendar
                                | 15 Dec 2017 - 25 Dec 2017
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-map-marker
                                | Monte Desert
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-group
                                | 10 People
                        div.events__btn(href="#events__card-modal-1")
                            i.events__btn-icon.icon-plus
                    .events__card-modal.mfp-hide#events__card-modal-1
                        .events__modal-img-wrap
                            picture
                                source(srcset="../assets/img/events-card-img1.webp", type="image/webp")
                                img.events__modal-img(src="../assets/img/events-card-img1.jpg", alt="black car")
                        .events__modal-content
                            .events__modal-row
                                        h2.events__modal-title About desert
                                        a.events__modal-dismiss(href="#"): i.icon-plus.events__modal-dismiss-icon
                            p.events__modal-text.
                                The Monte Desert is a South American ecoregion, lying entirely within Argentina and covering approximately the submontane areas of Catamarca, La Rioja, San Juan, San Luis and Mendoza Provinces, plus the western half of La Pampa Province and the extreme north of Río Negro Province. The desert lies southeast of the Atacama Desert in Chile, north of the larger Patagonian Desert, east of the Andes and west of the Sierra de Córdoba.
                li.events__card
                    .events__img-wrap
                        picture
                            source(srcset="../assets/img/events-card-img2.webp", type="image/webp")
                            img.events__img(src="../assets/img/events-card-img2.jpg", alt="cyclist on forest background")
                    .events__card-content
                        +title("Bitterroot Forest", "title_theme_card events__card-title")
                        ul.events__card-puncts
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-calendar
                                | 7 Jan 2018 - 9 jan 2018
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-map-marker
                                | Bitterroot Forest
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-group
                                | 13 People
                        div.events__btn(href="#events__card-modal-2")
                            i.events__btn-icon.icon-plus
                    .events__card-modal.mfp-hide#events__card-modal-2
                        .events__modal-img-wrap
                            picture
                                source(srcset="../assets/img/events-card-img2.webp", type="image/webp")
                                img.events__modal-img(src="../assets/img/events-card-img2.jpg", alt="black car")
                        .events__modal-content
                            .events__modal-row
                                    h2.events__modal-title Fascinating forest
                                    a.events__modal-dismiss(href="#"): i.icon-plus.events__modal-dismiss-icon
                            h3.events__modal-subtitle.
                                Bitterroot National Forest
                            h3.events__modal-subtitle.
                                Location: Near Missoula
                            h3.events__modal-subtitle.
                                Size: 1.6 million acres
                            p.events__modal-text.
                                Description: The Bitterroot National Forest encompasses 1.6 million acres, from the Idaho panhandle over the rugged Bitterroot Mountains to steep canyons that open to the valley floor. This mountain range is made up of rugged, remote terrain. Gentler than the Bitterroots, the Sapphire Mountains present a combination of grasslands and forested areas. The drier valley floor and lower foothills are an arid mix of grasslands and scrubland. Higher elevations receive more precipitation and are home to dense forests, alpine lakes, and clear, fast streams. The forest includes a large expanse of wilderness, including portions of the Selway-Bitterroot Wilderness and the Anaconda-Pintler Wilderness.
                li.events__card
                    .events__img-wrap
                        picture
                            source(srcset="../assets/img/events-card-img3.webp", type="image/webp")
                            img.events__img(src="../assets/img/events-card-img3.jpg", alt="car on a forest road")
                    .events__card-content
                        +title("Trans-Canadian Trail", "title_theme_card events__card-title")
                        ul.events__card-puncts
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-calendar
                                | 1 Feb 2018 - 5 Mar 2019
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-map-marker
                                | Trans-Canadian Trail
                            li.events__card-punct
                                span.events__card-icon-wrap
                                    i.events__card-icon.icon-group
                                | 19 People
                        div.events__btn(href="#events__card-modal-3")
                            i.events__btn-icon.icon-plus
                    .events__card-modal.mfp-hide#events__card-modal-3
                        .events__modal-img-wrap
                            picture
                                source(srcset="../assets/img/events-card-img3.webp", type="image/webp")
                                img.events__modal-img(src="../assets/img/events-card-img3.jpg", alt="black car")
                        .events__modal-content
                            .events__modal-row
                                h2.events__modal-title Longest trail
                                a.events__modal-dismiss(href="#"): i.icon-plus.events__modal-dismiss-icon
                            h3.events__modal-subtitle.
                                North America: Trans-Canadian Trail - 24,000 km
                            p.events__modal-text.
                                The longest walking route of the continent, and at the same time of the whole world, today is the Trans Canada Trail (Trans Canada Trail), which stretches from the city of Saint John on the east coast of Newfoundland Island (Atlantic) to the city of Victoria on Vancouver Island (in the Pacific Ocean) ). The trail, like all other mega routes, consists of a system of smaller roads connected together and united by common navigation, as well as specially built links between them. There are also water sections with a total length of 7000 km; it is proposed to overcome them by boats.